# IAM Policy RPCs in Artifact Registry Service

## SetIamPolicy
```
rpc SetIamPolicy(google.iam.v1.SetIamPolicyRequest)
    returns (google.iam.v1.Policy) {
  option (google.api.http) = {
    post: "/v1/{resource=projects/*/locations/*/repositories/*}:setIamPolicy"
    body: "*"
  };
}
```
**HTTP Method:** POST

## GetIamPolicy
```
rpc GetIamPolicy(google.iam.v1.GetIamPolicyRequest)
    returns (google.iam.v1.Policy) {
  option (google.api.http) = {
    get: "/v1/{resource=projects/*/locations/*/repositories/*}:getIamPolicy"
  };
}
```
**HTTP Method:** GET

## TestIamPermissions
```
rpc TestIamPermissions(google.iam.v1.TestIamPermissionsRequest)
    returns (google.iam.v1.TestIamPermissionsResponse) {
  option (google.api.http) = {
    post: "/v1/{resource=projects/*/locations/*/repositories/*}:testIamPermissions"
    body: "*"
  };
}
```
**HTTP Method:** POST

**Additional Notes:** No `additional_bindings` are specified for any of these three RPCs. All three operations target repository-level resources.

Based on the content provided, here is the complete `google.api.http` annotation for the `GetIamPolicy` RPC method:

```proto
option (google.api.http) = {
  post: "/v1/{resource=**}:getIamPolicy"
  body: "*"
};
```

**HTTP Method:** The annotation specifies `post` as the HTTP method.

**Additional Bindings:** There are no `additional_bindings` defined for this RPC method.

**Full Option Block:** The option block shown above represents the complete specification. It maps the `GetIamPolicy` RPC to an HTTP POST request with the path `/v1/{resource=**}:getIamPolicy`, where the entire request body is used as the message content.
